Package com.iontrading.mkv

Class MkvChain

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iontrading.mkv.MkvObject
      • com.iontrading.mkv.MkvChain
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable, Collection, List
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PrivateMkvChain
    @Keep
@KeepPublicClassMemberNames
public class MkvChain
extends MkvObject
implements List
    The MkvChain class wraps an ION Bus Chain in a Java Object.

    A Chain is an ordered collection of record names. Since it just stores the name of the records, there is no guarantee that contained records are available in the application.
    MkvChain objects may be subscribed via subscribe(MkvChainListener) method, subsequent updates to a subscribed chain are notified via MkvChainListener listener invocations.
    Since this class implements List interface (except subList method), it may be easily used with services of the Java Collections Framework.
    All methods can be called in concurrency and iterators can be safely used into a synchronized block.

    Unless otherwise noted, passing a null argument to a constructor or method in this class will cause a NullPointerException to be thrown.

    See Also:
    MkvObject, MkvChainListener, MkvPublishManager, MkvSubscribeManager

      • addAll

        public boolean addAll​(Collection c)
        Appends a Collection of record names to this MkvChain.

        If published and not in Edit mode, the ION Bus update event will be notified to all local and remote subscribers of this chain.

        Using this method causes the MkvChain to be reset and force re-subscription of the entire chain downstream. For this reason, the method has performance impact downstream.

      • subscribe

        public void subscribe​(MkvChainListener listener)
               throws MkvObjectNotAvailableException,
                      MkvConnectionException
        Subscribes this chain with the specified MkvChainListener.

        Updates on this MkvChain will be notified via the specified MkvChainListener listener invocations.

        Parameters:
        listener - the MkvChainListener to register.
        Throws:
        MkvObjectNotAvailableException - if this MkvChain is not available on the Platform.
        MkvConnectionException - if the connection with the publisher of this MkvChain has been broken.
        See Also:
        MkvChainListener, unsubscribe(MkvChainListener)

                                  String[] prefetchFields)
                           throws MkvObjectNotAvailableException,
                                  MkvConnectionException
        Subscribes this chain with the specified MkvChainListener, prefetching the specified set of fields from all the records in the chain.

        Updates on this MkvChain will be notified via the specified MkvChainListener listener invocations.

        Parameters:
        listener - the MkvChainListener to register.
        prefetchFields - the field list to prefetch data for all the chain records.

      • unsubscribe

        public void unsubscribe​(MkvChainListener listener)
                 throws MkvObjectNotAvailableException,
                        MkvConnectionException
        Removes the subscription made with the specified MkvChainListener.

        Unregisters the specified MkvChainListener from the listeners associated with this MkvChain and unsubscribes this chain if there are no more listener registered with it.

        Parameters:
        listener - the MkvChainListener to unregister.
        Throws:
        MkvObjectNotAvailableException - if this MkvChain is not available on the Platform.
        MkvConnectionException - if the connection with the publisher of this MkvChain has been broken.
        See Also:
        MkvChainListener, subscribe(MkvChainListener)

      • edit

        public void edit​(boolean editMode)
        Switches this MkvChain from edit to non-edit mode and viceversa.

        When exiting from edit mode if the chain has been modified, an update is sent to all subscribers of this chain.

        Parameters:
        editMode - specifies whether the edit mode is on or off
        Throws:
        MkvObjectNotLocalException - if this MkvChain has not been created by the application.
